<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,612,1324,1350]" box="[151,612,1324,1350]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,612,1324,1350]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,612,1324,1350]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Fairmaire, 1882" authorityName="Fairmaire" authorityYear="1882" box="[238,612,1324,1350]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Lydomorphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[238,404,1324,1350]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Lydomorphus</emphasis>
Fairmaire, 1882
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,1389,1774]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
This genus was revised by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kaszab" box="[466,638,1389,1414]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" refString="Kaszab, Z. (1955 a) Die Arten der Meloiden-Gattung Cylindrothorax Escher. (Coleoptera). Annales historico-naturales Musei nationalis Hungarici, New Series, 6, 225 - 258." type="journal article" year="1955" yearSuffix="a">Kaszab (1955a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kaszab" box="[653,712,1390,1414]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" refString="Kaszab, Z. (1978) Neue Meloiden aus Asien, Afrika uns Sudamerika (Coleoptera). Acta Z oologica Academiae scientiarum hungaricae, 24, 331 - 342." type="journal article" year="1978">1978</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName box="[758,930,1389,1413]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cylindrothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[758,930,1389,1413]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Cylindrothorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), while 
<bibRefCitation author="Selander" box="[1027,1436,1389,1414]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" refString="Selander, R. B. (1988 a) An annotated catalog and summary of bionomics of blister beetles of the genus Cylindrothorax (Coleoptera, Meloidae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 114, 15 - 70." type="journal article" year="1988" yearSuffix="a">
Selander (1988a as 
<taxonomicName box="[1255,1427,1389,1413]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cylindrothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1255,1427,1389,1413]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Cylindrothorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
)
</bibRefCitation>
summarized the distribution of all species. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bologna" box="[637,921,1425,1450]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" refString="Bologna, M. A. &amp; Aloisi, G. (1992) Systematics of Lydomorphus Fairmaire 1882, with a description of the first instar larva of L. dusaulti (Coleoptera Meloidae). Tropical Zoology, 5, 55 - 71. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 03946975.1992.10539182" type="journal article" year="1992">Bologna &amp; Aloisi (1992)</bibRefCitation>
described the first instar larva, evidenced the priority of the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fairmaire" authorityYear="1882" box="[383,536,1461,1485]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Lydomorphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[383,536,1461,1485]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Lydomorphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
over 
<taxonomicName box="[601,773,1461,1485]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cylindrothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[601,773,1461,1485]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Cylindrothorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and improved the infrageneric classification by describing two new subgenera. We accept here, with few exceptions, the groups of species proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kaszab" box="[1210,1387,1497,1522]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" refString="Kaszab, Z. (1955 a) Die Arten der Meloiden-Gattung Cylindrothorax Escher. (Coleoptera). Annales historico-naturales Musei nationalis Hungarici, New Series, 6, 225 - 258." type="journal article" year="1955" yearSuffix="a">Kaszab (1955a)</bibRefCitation>
and the subgenera described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bologna" box="[470,760,1533,1558]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" refString="Bologna, M. A. &amp; Aloisi, G. (1992) Systematics of Lydomorphus Fairmaire 1882, with a description of the first instar larva of L. dusaulti (Coleoptera Meloidae). Tropical Zoology, 5, 55 - 71. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 03946975.1992.10539182" type="journal article" year="1992">Bologna &amp; Aloisi (1992)</bibRefCitation>
. Most of the species of this genus, including the Namibian ones, are nocturnal or active also during the day.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,1389,1774]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
Recent research, based on adult (
<bibRefCitation author="Bologna" box="[564,818,1605,1630]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" refString="Bologna, M. A. &amp; Pinto, J. D. (2002) The Old World genera of Meloidae (Coleoptera): a key and synopsis. Journal of Natural History, 36, 2013 - 2102. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930110062318" type="journal article" year="2002">Bologna &amp; Pinto 2002</bibRefCitation>
) and larval morphology (Bologna 
<emphasis box="[1202,1258,1605,1629]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">et al.</emphasis>
in preparation), and on molecular data (Pitzalis et 
<emphasis box="[532,588,1641,1665]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">et al.</emphasis>
in preparation), pointed out the polyphyly of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fairmaire" authorityYear="1882" box="[1101,1254,1641,1665]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Lydomorphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1101,1254,1641,1665]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Lydomorphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Actually, some Palaeotropical and Saharan species belong to an undescribed genus (Pitzalis 
<emphasis box="[1036,1096,1677,1701]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">et al.</emphasis>
in preparation); one northern Namibian species (
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Peringuey" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[366,479,1714,1737]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Dilatilydus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="optatus">
<emphasis box="[366,479,1714,1737]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">L. optatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and another one from Namaqualand and Karoo (
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Peringuey" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[1044,1278,1713,1737]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Desertilydus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mesembryanthemi">
<emphasis box="[1044,1278,1713,1737]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">L. mesembryanthemi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) are referable to two new genera described below (
<taxonomicName authority="Bologna &amp; Amore &amp; Pitzalis, 2018" authorityName="Bologna &amp; Amore &amp; Pitzalis" authorityYear="2018" box="[563,688,1749,1773]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Dilatilydus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n">
<emphasis box="[563,688,1749,1773]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Dilatilydus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Bologna &amp; Amore &amp; Pitzalis, 2018" authorityName="Bologna &amp; Amore &amp; Pitzalis" authorityYear="2018" box="[742,883,1749,1773]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Desertilydus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n">
<emphasis box="[742,883,1749,1773]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Desertilydus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
